{"title_page": "Alex Pechin", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{short description|American football punter}}\n{{Infobox college football player|name=Alex Pechin|school=Bucknell Bison|birth_date={{Birth date and age|1996|11|18|mf=y}}|bowlgames=*[[2020 East-West Shrine Bowl]]|birth_place=[[Kennett Square, Pennsylvania]]|class={{Redshirt}} Senior|currentnumber=1|currentposition=[[Punter (football)|Punter]]|espn=3907928|height_ft=6|height_in=1|highlights=*[[Football Championship Subdivision|FCS]] Punting Average Leader (2019)|highschool=[[Unionville High School (Kennett Square, Pennsylvania)]]|pastschools=*[[Bucknell Bison football|Bucknell]] (2015\u20132019)|weight_lb=213}}\n\n'''Alex Pechin''' (born November 18, 1996) is an [[American football]] [[Punter (football)|punter]] for the [[Bucknell Bison football|Bucknell Bison]].\n\n== High school career ==\nPechin played high school football at [[Unionville High School (Kennett Square, Pennsylvania)|Unionville High School]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://247sports.com/Player/Alex-Pechin-46099712/high-school-248463/|title=Alex Pechin, Unionville , Punter|website=247Sports|language=en-US|access-date=March 22, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== College career ==\nPechin led the [[Football Championship Subdivision|FCS]] in punting average his senior season, with an average of 47.3 yards per punt.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ncaa.com/stats/football/fcs|title=NCAA College Football FCS current individual Stats {{!}} NCAA.com|website=www.ncaa.com|language=en|access-date=March 22, 2020}}</ref> For his efforts he was named FCS Punter of the Year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bucknellbison.com/news/2019/12/23/football-bucknells-alex-pechin-named-inaugural-fcs-punter-of-the-year.aspx|title=Bucknell's Alex Pechin Named Inaugural FCS Punter of the Year|website=Bucknell University Athletics|language=en|access-date=March 22, 2020}}</ref> He participated in the [[2020 East\u2013West Shrine Bowl|2020 East-West Shrine Bowl]] on January 18, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bucknellbison.com/news/2020/1/14/football-bucknells-alex-pechin-prepares-for-east-west-shrine-bowl.aspx|title=Bucknell's Alex Pechin Prepares for East-West Shrine Bowl|website=Bucknell University Athletics|language=en|access-date=March 22, 2020}}</ref> He was named to the STATS FCS All-Decade Team.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://patriotleague.org/news/2020/1/1/football-bucknells-alex-pechin-selected-to-stats-fcs-all-decade-team.aspx|title=Bucknell's Alex Pechin Selected to STATS FCS All-Decade Team|website=patriotleague.org|language=en|access-date=March 22, 2020}}</ref> Pechin was the only player from the [[Patriot League]] to attend the 2020 [[NFL Scouting Combine]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.heraldbulletin.com/sports/punter-pechin-representing-bucknell-and-entire-patriot-league-at-nfl/article_8b8b5456-58c7-11ea-85c1-0f710020e473.html|title=Punter Pechin representing Bucknell and entire Patriot League at NFL Combine|last=Bulletin|first=Joe Frollo For The Herald|website=Herald Bulletin|language=en|access-date=March 22, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Professional career ==\n{{NFL predraft|height ft=6|height in=1|weight=213|arm span=29 5/8|hand span=9 3/8|dash=4.69|bench=13|vertical=34.0|note=All values from NFL Combine<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nfl.com/prospects/alexander-pechin?id=32195045-4317-1607-18be-b7afa3d0bb42 |access-date=March 22, 2020}}</ref>}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pechin, Alex}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American football punters]]\n[[Category:Bucknell Bison football players]]\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Players of American football from Pennsylvania]]\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{short description|American football punter}}\n{{Infobox college football player|name=Alex Pechin|school=Bucknell Bison|birth_date={{Birth date and age|1996|11|18|mf=y}}|bowlgames=*[[2020 East-West Shrine Bowl]]|birth_place=[[Kennett Square, Pennsylvania]]|class={{Redshirt}} Senior|currentnumber=1|currentposition=[[Punter (football)|Punter]]|espn=3907928|height_ft=6|height_in=1|highlights=*[[Football Championship Subdivision|FCS]] Punting Average Leader (2019)|highschool=[[Unionville High School (Kennett Square, Pennsylvania)]]|pastschools=*[[Bucknell Bison football|Bucknell]] (2015\u20132019)|weight_lb=213}}\n\n'''Alex Pechin''' (born November 18, 1996) is an [[American football]] [[Punter (football)|punter]] for the [[Bucknell Bison football|Bucknell Bison]].\n\n== High school career ==\nPechin played high school football at [[Unionville High School (Kennett Square, Pennsylvania)|Unionville High School]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://247sports.com/Player/Alex-Pechin-46099712/high-school-248463/|title=Alex Pechin, Unionville , Punter|website=247Sports|language=en-US|access-date=March 22, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== College career ==\nPechin led the [[Football Championship Subdivision|FCS]] in punting average his senior season, with an average of 47.3 yards per punt.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ncaa.com/stats/football/fcs|title=NCAA College Football FCS current individual Stats {{!}} NCAA.com|website=www.ncaa.com|language=en|access-date=March 22, 2020}}</ref> For his efforts he was named FCS Punter of the Year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bucknellbison.com/news/2019/12/23/football-bucknells-alex-pechin-named-inaugural-fcs-punter-of-the-year.aspx|title=Bucknell's Alex Pechin Named Inaugural FCS Punter of the Year|website=Bucknell University Athletics|language=en|access-date=March 22, 2020}}</ref> He participated in the [[2020 East\u2013West Shrine Bowl|2020 East-West Shrine Bowl]] on January 18, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bucknellbison.com/news/2020/1/14/football-bucknells-alex-pechin-prepares-for-east-west-shrine-bowl.aspx|title=Bucknell's Alex Pechin Prepares for East-West Shrine Bowl|website=Bucknell University Athletics|language=en|access-date=March 22, 2020}}</ref> He was named to the STATS FCS All-Decade Team.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://patriotleague.org/news/2020/1/1/football-bucknells-alex-pechin-selected-to-stats-fcs-all-decade-team.aspx|title=Bucknell's Alex Pechin Selected to STATS FCS All-Decade Team|website=patriotleague.org|language=en|access-date=March 22, 2020}}</ref> Pechin was the only player from the [[Patriot League]] to attend the 2020 [[NFL Scouting Combine]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.heraldbulletin.com/sports/punter-pechin-representing-bucknell-and-entire-patriot-league-at-nfl/article_8b8b5456-58c7-11ea-85c1-0f710020e473.html|title=Punter Pechin representing Bucknell and entire Patriot League at NFL Combine|last=Bulletin|first=Joe Frollo For The Herald|website=Herald Bulletin|language=en|access-date=March 22, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Professional career ==\n{{NFL predraft|height ft=6|height in=1|weight=213|arm span=29 5/8|hand span=9 3/8|dash=4.69|bench=13|vertical=34.0|note=All values from NFL Combine<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nfl.com/prospects/alexander-pechin?id=32195045-4317-1607-18be-b7afa3d0bb42 |access-date=March 22, 2020}}</ref>}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pechin, Alex}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American football punters]]\n[[Category:Bucknell Bison football players]]\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Players of American football from Pennsylvania]]\n", "name_user": "Joeykai", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:clean up, removed orphan tag", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alex_Pechin"}
{"title_page": "Kevin Dotson (American football)", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Infobox college football player\n| name            = Kevin Dotson\n| image           = \n| image_size      =\n| alt             =\n| caption         = \n| highschool      = [[Plaquemine High School]]<br>([[Plaquemine, Louisiana]])\n| school          = Louisiana Ragin' Cajuns\n| currentnumber   = 75\n| currentposition = [[Offensive guard]]/[[offensive tackle]]\n| class           = {{redshirt}} [[Senior (education)|Senior]]\n| major           = General Studies\n| birth_date      = \n| birth_place     = \n| height_ft       = 6\n| height_in       = 4\n| weight_lb       = 321\n| bowlgames       =\n*[[2020 LendingTree Bowl]]\n| highlights      =\n*2x First team All-[[Sun Belt Conference|Sun Belt]] ([[2018 Sun Belt Conference football season|2018]], [[2019 Sun Belt Conference football season|2019]])\n*Second team All-Sun Belt ([[2017 Sun Belt Conference football season|2017]])\n| pastschools     =\n* [[Louisiana Ragin' Cajuns football|Louisiana]] (2015\u20132019)\n|espn=3917599\n}}\n\n'''Kevin Dotson''' is an American football [[offensive guard]] and [[offensive tackle]] who currently plays for the [[Louisiana Ragin' Cajuns football|Louisiana Ragin' Cajuns]].\n\n==Early life and high school==\nDotson was born in [[West Point, Mississippi]] and grew up in [[Plaquemine, Louisiana]]. He attended [[Plaquemine High School]], where he played football with his twin brother Kenny.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theadvocate.com/acadiana/sports/ul_lafayette/article_af34373a-7b92-11e6-9a9f-d7d69c7e0d13.html|title=After rough start, Kevin Dotson emerges as starter on Cajuns' offensive line|first=Raymond|last=Partsch II|work=[[The Advocate (Louisiana)|The Advocate]]|date=September 15, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==College career==\nDotson [[redshirt (college sports)|redshirted]] his true freshman season. He became the Ragin' Cajuns right guard two weeks into his redshirt freshman and was named to the [[Sun Belt Conference]] All-Newcomer Team.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.postsouth.com/sports/20170727/former-devil-performing-well-at-next-level|title=Former Devil performing well at next level|first=Andrew|last=Green|work=[[Plaquemine Post South]]|date=July 27, 2017}}</ref> Dotson was named second team All-Sun Belt as a redshirt sophomore after starting all 12 of Louisiana's games.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theadvocate.com/acadiana/sports/ul_lafayette/article_5d8e6408-a65d-11e8-be83-0f71529df1d2.html|title=UL-Lafayette offensive line primed to put recent struggles behind them|work=The Advocate|date=August 22, 2020}}</ref> He was named firs team All-Sun Belt as a redshirt junior after starting 14 games at right guard.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theadvertiser.com/story/sports/college/ul/2019/08/21/ul-lafayette-louisiana-ragin-cajuns-football-kevin-dotson-sets-high-expectations-himself-and-team/2074043001/|title=Cajuns' Kevin Dotson sets high expectations for himself and team|work=The Daily Advertiser|date=August 21, 2019}}</ref> Dotson started all 14 of the Rajin' Cajuns games and was again named first team All-Sun Belt as a redshirt senior an was also named a first team All-American by the [[Associated Press]] and to the second team by the ''[[Sporting News]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theadvertiser.com/story/sports/college/ul/2019/12/16/ull-football-cajuns-nfl-prospect-hunt-to-miss-lendingtree-senior-bowls/2662270001/|title=UL's Dotson named AP All-American; Hunt to miss bowls|work=The Daily Advertiser|date=December 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://ragincajuns.com/sports/football/roster/kevin-dotson/6854 Louisiana Ragin' Cajuns bio]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dotson, Kevin}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American football offensive guards]]\n[[Category:Players of American football from Louisiana]]\n[[Category:Louisiana Ragin' Cajuns football players]]\n[[Category:People from Plaquemine, Louisiana]]\n[[Category:People from West Point, Mississippi]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox college football player\n| name            = Kevin Dotson\n| image           = \n| image_size      =\n| alt             =\n| caption         = \n| highschool      = [[Plaquemine High School]]<br>([[Plaquemine, Louisiana]])\n| school          = Louisiana Ragin' Cajuns\n| currentnumber   = 75\n| currentposition = [[Offensive guard]]/[[offensive tackle]]\n| class           = {{redshirt}} [[Senior (education)|Senior]]\n| major           = General Studies\n| birth_date      = \n| birth_place     = \n| height_ft       = 6\n| height_in       = 4\n| weight_lb       = 321\n| bowlgames       =\n*[[2020 LendingTree Bowl]]\n| highlights      =\n*2x First team All-[[Sun Belt Conference|Sun Belt]] ([[2018 Sun Belt Conference football season|2018]], [[2019 Sun Belt Conference football season|2019]])\n*Second team All-Sun Belt ([[2017 Sun Belt Conference football season|2017]])\n| pastschools     =\n* [[Louisiana Ragin' Cajuns football|Louisiana]] (2015\u20132019)\n|espn=3917599\n}}\n\n'''Kevin Dotson''' is an American football [[offensive guard]] and [[offensive tackle]] who currently plays for the [[Louisiana Ragin' Cajuns football|Louisiana Ragin' Cajuns]].\n\n==Early life and high school==\nDotson was born in [[West Point, Mississippi]] and grew up in [[Plaquemine, Louisiana]]. He attended [[Plaquemine High School]], where he played football with his twin brother Kenny.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theadvocate.com/acadiana/sports/ul_lafayette/article_af34373a-7b92-11e6-9a9f-d7d69c7e0d13.html|title=After rough start, Kevin Dotson emerges as starter on Cajuns' offensive line|first=Raymond|last=Partsch II|work=[[The Advocate (Louisiana)|The Advocate]]|date=September 15, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==College career==\nDotson [[redshirt (college sports)|redshirted]] his true freshman season. He became the Ragin' Cajuns right guard two weeks into his redshirt freshman and was named to the [[Sun Belt Conference]] All-Newcomer Team.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.postsouth.com/sports/20170727/former-devil-performing-well-at-next-level|title=Former Devil performing well at next level|first=Andrew|last=Green|work=[[Plaquemine Post South]]|date=July 27, 2017}}</ref> Dotson was named second team All-Sun Belt as a redshirt sophomore after starting all 12 of Louisiana's games.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theadvocate.com/acadiana/sports/ul_lafayette/article_5d8e6408-a65d-11e8-be83-0f71529df1d2.html|title=UL-Lafayette offensive line primed to put recent struggles behind them|work=The Advocate|date=August 22, 2020}}</ref> He was named firs team All-Sun Belt as a redshirt junior after starting 14 games at right guard.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theadvertiser.com/story/sports/college/ul/2019/08/21/ul-lafayette-louisiana-ragin-cajuns-football-kevin-dotson-sets-high-expectations-himself-and-team/2074043001/|title=Cajuns' Kevin Dotson sets high expectations for himself and team|work=The Daily Advertiser|date=August 21, 2019}}</ref> Dotson started all 14 of the Rajin' Cajuns games and was again named first team All-Sun Belt as a redshirt senior an was also named a first team All-American by the [[Associated Press]] and to the second team by the ''[[Sporting News]]''. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theadvertiser.com/story/sports/college/ul/2019/12/16/ull-football-cajuns-nfl-prospect-hunt-to-miss-lendingtree-senior-bowls/2662270001/|title=UL's Dotson named AP All-American; Hunt to miss bowls|work=The Daily Advertiser|date=December 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://ragincajuns.com/sports/football/roster/kevin-dotson/6854 Louisiana Ragin' Cajuns bio]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dotson, Kevin}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American football offensive guards]]\n[[Category:Players of American football from Louisiana]]\n[[Category:Louisiana Ragin' Cajuns football players]]\n[[Category:People from Plaquemine, Louisiana]]\n[[Category:People fro