{"title_page": "Apex Designs Entertainment", "text_new": "<!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n{{Article for deletion/dated|page=Apex Designs Entertainment|timestamp=20200424084616|year=2020|month=April|day=24|substed=yes|help=off}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=Apex Designs Entertainment|date=24 April 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n{{Short description|Video game developer and publisher}}\n\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Apex Designs Entertainment\n| logo = ApexDesignsEntertainmentLogo2012.png\n| logo_caption = Logo in use on the Apex Designs website since 2012\n| industry = [[Video game industry|Video games]]\n| founded = {{Start date and age|df=yes|1994}}\n| founder = James Daniels\n| hq_location_city = [[Banbury]]\n| hq_location_country = England\n| products = {{Unbulleted list|''[[Payback (video game)|Payback]]''|''[[Payback 2]]''}}\n| website = {{URL|https://www.apex-designs.net}}\n}}\n\n'''Apex Designs Entertainment''', or simply '''Apex Designs''', is a self-publishing [[video game]] [[Video game developer|development]] company based in [[Banbury]], England.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.linkedin.com/company/apex-designs-entertainment-ltd|title=Apex Designs Entertainment Ltd|last=|first=|date=|website=Linkedin|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref> It is known for developing and publishing the video games [[Payback (video game)|''Payback'']] (2001), and its remake/sequel,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/gaming/2012/9/21/3368884/payback-2-developer-explains-changes-to-multiplayer-and-controls|title='Payback 2' developer explains changes to multiplayer and controls|last=Sarkar|first=Samit|date=2012-09-21|website=Polygon|language=en|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref> [[Payback 2|''Payback 2'']] (2012).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.apex-designs.net/games.html|title=Apex Designs - Games|last=|first=|date=|website=www.apex-designs.net|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nApex Designs Entertainment Ltd. was founded in 1994 by James Daniels.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mobygames.com/company/apex-designs/history|title=History for Apex Designs|website=MobyGames|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref> Its first game, ''Payback'', was released for the [[Amiga]] in 2001. Because of its success, the next year Apex Designs began work on a [[Game Boy Advance]] version which was released in 2004, a [[Macintosh]] version which was released in 2003,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://macintoshgarden.org/games/payback|title=Payback - Macintosh Garden|website=macintoshgarden.org|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref> and a [[GP2X]] version which was released in 2006.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.videogamer.com/news/payback-released-for-gp2x|title=Payback released for GP2X|website=VideoGamer.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref> In 2008, Apex Designs also released a version of ''Payback'' for [[iOS]], with the same features as the GP2X version.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pocketgamer.com/articles/011491/interview-apex-designs-fills-us-in-on-payback-and-the-pitfalls-of-iphone-development/|title=Interview: Apex Designs fills us in on Payback and the pitfalls of iPhone development|last=Spencer|first=Spanner|website=www.pocketgamer.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref> \n\nIn 2012, Apex Designs released ''Payback''<nowiki/>'s remake/sequel, ''Payback 2'', for [[iOS]] and this time [[Android (operating system)|Android]] too.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/ios/payback-2---the-battle-sandbox|title=Payback 2 - The Battle Sandbox|website=Metacritic|language=en|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref> ''Payback 2'' started significantly rising in popularity in 2016, and has kept rising since.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://trends.google.com/trends/explore?date=all&q=/g/11gcngl_3z|title=Google Trends|website=Google Trends|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref>\n\nDespite the ''Payback'' games being [[Grand Theft Auto|GTA]] clones, even copying car names such as the \"Mundaneo\", [[Rockstar Games]] has made no attempt to stop Apex Designs from publishing the games, or even warn them about infringing on their copyrighted materials.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://toucharcade.com/2009/01/28/a-look-at-gta-like-payback-for-iphone-and-ipod-touch/|title=A Look at GTA-like 'Payback' for iPhone and iPod touch|date=2009-01-28|website=TouchArcade|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n[[Category:Video game development companies]]\n[[Category:Video game developers]]\n", "text_old": "<!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n{{Article for deletion/dated|page=Apex Designs Entertainment|timestamp=20200424084616|year=2020|month=April|day=24|substed=yes|help=off}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=Apex Designs Entertainment|date=24 April 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n{{Short description|Video game developer and publisher}}\n\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Apex Designs Entertainment\n| logo = ApexDesignsEntertainmentLogo2012.png\n| logo_caption = Logo in use on the Apex Designs website since 2012\n| industry = [[Video game industry|Video games]]\n| founded = {{Start date and age|df=yes|1994}}\n| founder = James Daniels\n| hq_location_city = [[Banbury]]\n| hq_location_country = England\n| products = {{Unbulleted list|''[[Payback (video game)|Payback]]''|''[[Payback 2]]''}}\n| website = {{URL|https://www.apex-designs.net}}\n}}\n\n'''Apex Designs Entertainment''', or simply '''Apex Designs''', is a self-publishing [[video game]] [[Video game developer|development]] company based in [[Banbury]], England.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.linkedin.com/company/apex-designs-entertainment-ltd|title=Apex Designs Entertainment Ltd|last=|first=|date=|website=Linkedin|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref> It is known for developing and publishing the video games [[Payback (video game)|''Payback'']] (2001), and its remake/sequel,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/gaming/2012/9/21/3368884/payback-2-developer-explains-changes-to-multiplayer-and-controls|title='Payback 2' developer explains changes to multiplayer and controls|last=Sarkar|first=Samit|date=2012-09-21|website=Polygon|language=en|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref> [[Payback 2|''Payback 2'']] (2012).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.apex-designs.net/games.html|title=Apex Designs - Games|last=|first=|date=|website=www.apex-designs.net|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nApex Designs Entertainment Ltd. was founded in 1994 by James Daniels.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mobygames.com/company/apex-designs/history|title=History for Apex Designs|website=MobyGames|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref> It's first game, ''Payback'', was released for the [[Amiga]] in 2001. Because of it's success, the next year Apex Designs began work on a [[Game Boy Advance]] version which was released in 2004, a [[Macintosh]] version which was released in 2003,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://macintoshgarden.org/games/payback|title=Payback - Macintosh Garden|website=macintoshgarden.org|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref> and a [[GP2X]] version which was released in 2006.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.videogamer.com/news/payback-released-for-gp2x|title=Payback released for GP2X|website=VideoGamer.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref> In 2008, Apex Designs also released a version of ''Payback'' for [[iOS]], with the same features as the GP2X version.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pocketgamer.com/articles/011491/interview-apex-designs-fills-us-in-on-payback-and-the-pitfalls-of-iphone-development/|title=Interview: Apex Designs fills us in on Payback and the pitfalls of iPhone development|last=Spencer|first=Spanner|website=www.pocketgamer.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref> \n\nIn 2012, Apex Designs released ''Payback''<nowiki/>'s remake/sequel, ''Payback 2'', for [[iOS]] and this time [[Android (operating system)|Android]] too.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/ios/payback-2---the-battle-sandbox|title=Payback 2 - The Battle Sandbox|website=Metacritic|language=en|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref> ''Payback 2'' started significantly rising in popularity in 2016, and has kept rising since.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://trends.google.com/trends/explore?date=all&q=/g/11gcngl_3z|title=Google Trends|website=Google Trends|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref>\n\nDespite the ''Payback'' games being [[Grand Theft Auto|GTA]] clones, even copying car names such as the \"Mundaneo\", [[Rockstar Games]] has made no attempt to stop Apex Designs from publishing the games, or even warn them about infringing on their copyrighted materials.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://toucharcade.com/2009/01/28/a-look-at-gta-like-payback-for-iphone-and-ipod-touch/|title=A Look at GTA-like 'Payback' for iPhone and iPod touch|date=2009-01-28|website=TouchArcade|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n[[Category:Video game development companies]]\n[[Category:Video game developers]]\n", "name_user": "Neils51", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eHistory:spelling - it's->its", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apex_Designs_Entertainment"}
